Q.1. Who has written the poetry, “The Empty Heart”?
(A) Vidyapati
(B) Puran Singh
(C) Periasamy Thooran
(D) Amrita Pritam
Answer: (C) Periasamy Thooran
Explanation: The poem “The Empty Heart” is written by Periasamy Thooran, a Tamil writer and poet.

Q.2. What was the problem of the man?
(A) he was very dissatisfied
(B) he was very much in threat
(C) he had a crisis of money
(D) None of these
Answer: (A) he was very dissatisfied
Explanation: The man was not poor but he was dissatisfied and greedy.

Q.3. What did he demand from the tree?
(A) Pot of Gold
(B) Pot of Silver
(C) Pot of Bronze
(D) Pot of Copper
Answer: (A) Pot of Gold
Explanation: The man asked the magical tree for pots of gold.

Q.4. What happened to his prayer?
(A) Prayers were not granted
(B) Prayers were granted
(C) Prayers were neither granted nor refused
(D) None of these
Answer: (B) Prayers were granted
Explanation: The tree granted his prayer and gave him gold.

Q.5. What were in Pitchers?
(A) Gold Coins
(B) Silver Coins
(C) Copper Coins
(D) None of these
Answer: (A) Gold Coins
Explanation: The pitchers were full of gold coins.

Q.6. Greed is ………….but life is not.
(A) Worthy
(B) Bad
(C) Good
(D) Endless
Answer: (D) Endless
Explanation: The poem says greed is endless, but life is short.

Q.7. This poem tells about the problems caused by:
(A) Sickness
(B) Poverty
(C) Overeating
(D) Greed
Answer: (D) Greed
Explanation: The poem shows that greed causes unhappiness and problems.

Q.8. There was a…………….which had the power to grant wishes.
(A) Snake
(B) Pigeon
(C) Tree
(D) Temple
Answer: (C) Tree
Explanation: A magical tree had the power to grant wishes.

Q.9. The tree gave the man seven…………..full of gold coins.
(A) Pots/Pitchers
(B) Pans
(C) Bags
(D) Sacks
Answer: (A) Pots/Pitchers
Explanation: The tree gave him seven pitchers full of gold coins.

Q.10. The man tried all tricks to gather:
(A) Silver
(B) Diamonds
(C) Jewellery
(D) Gold
Answer: (D) Gold
Explanation: The man became greedy and tried to collect more and more gold.

Q.11. What made him mad?
(A) His Greedy tendency
(B) His tendency of getting more & more
(C) Sudden shock
(D) None of these
Answer: (B) His tendency of getting more & more
Explanation: His greed and desire for more gold made him mad.

Q.12. What is Kalpaka?
(A) a tree
(B) a big tree
(C) a golden tree
(D) wish-yielding tree
Answer: (D) wish-yielding tree
Explanation: Kalpaka is a wish-yielding tree that grants wishes.

Q.13. Each coin he could clutch by hook or:
(A) shook
(B) look
(C) crook
(D) took
Answer: (C) crook
Explanation: The phrase “by hook or crook” means by any method.

Q.14. The poem, ‘The Empty Heart’ is translated from:
(A) English
(B) Oriya
(C) Bengali
(D) Tamil
Answer: (D) Tamil
Explanation: The poem was originally written in Tamil and later translated.

Q.15. Periasamy Thooran was born in:
(A) 1708
(B) 1809
(C) 1908
(D) 1988
Answer: (C) 1908
Explanation: Periasamy Thooran was born in 1908.

Q.16. Periasamy Thooran, the poet died in:
(A) 1908
(B) 1988
(C) 1987
(D) 1897
Answer: (C) 1987
Explanation: He died in 1987.

Q.17. Periasamy Thooran was a ________ writer.
(A) Bengali
(B) Marathi
(C) Punjabi
(D) Tamil
Answer: (D) Tamil
Explanation: He was a Tamil writer.

Q.18. Why was the man not content, although he was rich?
(A) due to thirst of gold
(B) due to thirst of wealth
(C) (A) and (B) both
(D) none of these
Answer: (C) (A) and (B) both
Explanation: The man was greedy and wanted more gold and wealth.

Q.19. Periasamy Thooran first made his name as a writer of:
(A) essay
(B) Short stories and poems
(C) Poem
(D) satire
Answer: (B) Short stories and poems
Explanation: He first became famous for short stories and poems.

Q.20. The poet asks the Koel, what has ________ her.
(A) hurt
(B) forgotten
(C) told
(D) longings
Answer: (A) hurt
Explanation: The poet asks the Koel what has hurt her.

Q.21. The high-pitched strains of the Koel wake in the poet’s soul a:
(A) dreams
(B) desires
(C) memories
(D) longings
Answer: (C) memories
Explanation: The Koel’s song awakens memories in the poet’s mind.

Q.22. The man’s prayer was granted:
(A) quick
(B) late
(C) gold coins
(D) sevenfold
Answer: (D) sevenfold
Explanation: The man received seven pitchers of gold.

Q.23. How many pitchers did the man get as a gift?
(A) one
(B) three
(C) Six
(D) Seven
Answer: (D) Seven
Explanation: The man received seven pitchers of gold coins.

Q.24. Because he did not eat, drink or sleep properly, his health:
(A) became sound
(B) got down
(C) broke down
(D) None of these
Answer: (C) broke down
Explanation: Due to greed, he stopped caring for his health and became ill.

Q.25. Morning, noon and……. …. he went.
(A) day
(B) afternoon
(C) night
(D) midnight
Answer: (C) night
Explanation: He kept collecting gold day and night.

Q.26. His prayer was granted:
(A) eight fold
(B) sevenfold
(C) six fold
(D) five fold
Answer: (B) sevenfold
Explanation: He received seven pitchers of gold.

Q.27. For as a gift to him was ________.
(A) granted
(B) gifted
(C) offered
(D) given
Answer: (D) given
Explanation: The correct word in the poem line is “given”.

Q.28. To ________ all this was his thought.
(A) steadily
(B) quick
(C) sharply
(D) shortly
Answer: (B) quick
Explanation: His mind was always thinking about gold quickly.

Q.29. The seven full ________ he clean forgot.
(A) pots
(B) pitchers
(C) pictures
(D) vessels
Answer: (D) vessels
Explanation: Vessels means pitchers filled with gold.

Q.30. Nothing is wrong with a half-filled purse, ‘Tis the void in the heart:
(A) that is the curse
(B) that is the purse
(C) that is the gold
(D) that is the wealth
Answer: (A) that is the curse
Explanation: The poem says the real problem is an empty heart, not lack of money.

Q.31. The ________ demon now made him mad.
(A) fire
(B) gold
(C) silver pot
(D) Desire
Answer: (D) Desire
Explanation: Desire (greed) made him mad.
